==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Marquis
<hw>Mar"quis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>marquis</ets>, OF. <ets>markis</ets>, <ets>marchis</ets>, LL.
<ets>marchensis</ets>; of German origin; cf. G. <ets>mark</ets> bound,
border, march, OHG. <ets>marcha</ets>. See <er>March</er> border, and
cf. <er>Marchioness</er>, <er>Marquee</er>, <er>Marquess</er>.]</ety>
<def>A nobleman in England, France, and Germany, of a rank next below
that of duke. Originally, the marquis was an officer whose duty was to
guard the marches or frontiers of the kingdom. The office has ceased,
and the name is now a mere title conferred by patent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Marquisate</ent>⟦br⟧
